definition: to sign one's name/visa/variant of 籤|签[qian1]
to set/to fix/to determine/to decide/to order

sentences.english: The purchaser signing the subscription document must be cautious and avoid falling into the trap.
sentences.chinese: 購買人簽定樓宇認購書應謹防誤入陷阱。

sentences.english: Everybody has seen the face of the movement before and after the 12-point understanding.
sentences.chinese: 所有人都看到了12點協議簽定後運動發生的變化。

sentences.english: IN WITNESS WHEREOF I cause this Power of Attorney to be duly signed.
sentences.chinese: 作爲證據，本人於此正式簽定本授權委宛書。

sentences.english: Most try to sign a divorce settlementby themselves first.
sentences.chinese: 大多數夫妻會先行簽定離婚協議書。

sentences.english: He's got a five-year deal with the Major League Soccer club.
sentences.chinese: 他同這支大聯盟球隊簽定了爲期五年的合同。
他們簽定了互不侵犯條約。

sentences.english: He said Raila Odina could not sign up to a cabinet that he did not agree too.
sentences.chinese: 表示R總統將不會與一個他不同意的內閣簽定協議。

sentences.english: I was one of the first Castaways to be offered a place, and the last to sign the contract.
sentences.chinese: 我是第一個被選出來最後一個簽定合同的漂流者。

sentences.english: This tab is located at the extreme right of the list of tabs.
sentences.chinese: 這個頁簽定位在頁籤列表的最右邊。

sentences.english: This Agreement will be effective upon the execution of this Agreement by the Parties.
sentences.chinese: 本合約自甲乙雙方簽定後，始生效力。

sentences.english: A: Before you sign the lease, do you have any questions?
sentences.chinese: 簽定租契之前，你有什麼問題嗎？

sentences.english: According to these articles did the Romans covenant with the people of the Jews.
sentences.chinese: 根據這些話，羅馬人同猶太民族簽定了盟約。

sentences.english: An agreement to be signed (=which is to be signed) next week will concern every ont of us.
sentences.chinese: 下週要簽定的一項協定關係的我們每一個人。

sentences.english: The storekeeper signed a complaint accusing them of shoplifting.
sentences.chinese: 店東簽定了控訴書，指控他們在店裏扒竊貨色。
